This paper deals with managing Quality of Service (QoS) for multimedia flows transmitted over a network, specifically in the context of High Speed Downlink Packet Access (HSDPA) networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses mathematical modeling and numerical results, indicating that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The focus on multimedia flows suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses queue management and scheduling schemes, which could fall under cs.PF (Performance).
